TY  - JOUR
T1  - Mingling Decision Making Metaphors
AU  - Meyer, Alan D.
Y1  - 1984/01/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1984.4277746
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1984.4277746
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 6
EP  - 17
VL  - 9
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Organizational decisions provide conceptual playing fields wherein scientists adhering to rival theories based on different metaphors skirmish indecisively. Organizational decisions, however, are also empirical arenas wherein practitioners espousing discordant theories-in-use reconcile their differences pragmatically. Practitioners' decision-making metaphors encountered while studying capital budgeting suggest how disjoint perspectives are assimilated and shifts from instrumental to symbolic actions are triggered. Implications for decision theories are discussed, and potential benefits of incorporating practitioners' knowledge into organizational science are considered.
AB  - Organizational decisions provide conceptual playing fields wherein scientists adhering to rival theories based on different metaphors skirmish indecisively. Organizational decisions, however, are also empirical arenas wherein practitioners espousing discordant theories-in-use reconcile their differences pragmatically. Practitioners' decision-making metaphors encountered while studying capital budgeting suggest how disjoint perspectives are assimilated and shifts from instrumental to symbolic actions are triggered. Implications for decision theories are discussed, and potential benefits of incorporating practitioners' knowledge into organizational science are considered.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1984.4277746
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1984.4277746
Y2  - 2026/04/24
